. EBS (Elastic Block Store) ‚Äî Key Points (Exam Focus)
üìå Definition
EBS = Durable block-level storage that attaches to EC2.
Works like a hard disk for EC2.

üìå Key Features
Block storage ‚Üí low latency reads/writes.
Attached to a single EC2 (except Multi-Attach for io2).
Persists even after EC2 stops/terminates (unless delete-on-termination=true).
Can attach multiple EBS volumes to a single EC2.
Volume and EC2 must be in same AZ (Exam HOT).

2. EBS Volume Modifications
You can modify LIVE volumes (no downtime):
Increase Size
Increase IOPS
Change Volume Type (gp2 ‚Üí gp3, gp3 ‚Üí io1 etc.)
üëâ Exam Tip: Only works for current generation EC2 + EBS.

3. Use Cases
OS boot volume
Databases (MySQL/Postgres)
Applications needing frequent updates
High-throughput workloads (log processing, analytics)

4. EBS Multi-Attach (Exam-Specific)
Supported ONLY for io2 volumes
Can attach one EBS volume to multiple EC2 instances (same AZ).
For clustered Linux apps, shared file systems.
NOT for Windows, NOT for root volume.

5. EBS Encryption (AES-256 + KMS)
üìå Uses KMS Keys
Encryption uses AWS KMS.
Algorithm: AES-256 (Exam must-remember).

üìå Encryption happens on EC2 host
NOT on EBS.
So data at rest + data in transit (EC2 ‚Üí EBS) is encrypted.

üìå What Gets Encrypted Automatically
Data inside the EBS volume
Data in transit between EC2 ‚Üî EBS
Snapshots of encrypted volumes
Volumes created from encrypted snapshots

üëâ Exam Trick:
Encrypted ‚Üí snapshot is encrypted ‚Üí new volume is encrypted.
Unencrypted ‚Üí snapshot unencrypted unless explicitly encrypted.

6. How to Encrypt an Existing Unencrypted Volume
Steps:
Take snapshot (unencrypted)
Copy snapshot ‚Üí choose Encrypt
Create new volume from encrypted snapshot
Attach to EC2

7. EC2 Key Pairs (SSH Authentication)
üìå Key Pair = Public Key + Private Key
Used for SSH authentication into EC2.
Public Key
Stored on EC2 instance under:
~/.ssh/authorized_keys
Private Key (.pem file)
Stored by you
Required for SSH login
If lost ‚Üí cannot recover (Exam point)
Login Requirement
ssh -i mykey.pem ec2-user@public-ip
Security Rule
Never check .pem into GitHub.
Anyone with private key gets full access.

8. Boot Behavior
When EC2 boots first time, it injects the public key into the OS.

For Linux:
Default users: ec2-user, ubuntu, centos, etc.

9. Common Exam Use Cases
Case 1: Lost Private Key
‚ùå You can‚Äôt recover it
‚úî Only solution:
Create new key pair
Stop instance
Detach root volume
Attach to another EC2
Add new public key manually
Reattach and boot

Case 2: Need to Encrypt Existing Volume
Snapshot ‚Üí Copy snapshot (encrypted) ‚Üí Create new volume

Case 3: EC2 can't access unencrypted + encrypted volumes together?
‚úî It CAN. (Exam trick question)

Case 4: Same EBS volume attached to multiple EC2?
‚úî Only using io2 Multi-Attach

‚ùå Not supported for boot/root volume

Case 5: EBS AZ Restriction
Volume & EC2 must be in same AZ

10. Super Quick Revision (30 Seconds Before Exam)
EBS = Block storage
S3 = Object storage
Encryption = KMS + AES-256
Encryption covers: data at rest + transit + snapshots + derived volumes
Modify EBS volume live (size/IOPS/type)
Multi-Attach ‚Üí io2 volume ‚áí multiple EC2
Lose private key = no recovery
Key injected to: ~/.ssh/authorized_keys


MCQs: EC2 + EBS + Encryption + Key Pairs
1. EBS is what type of storage?
A. Object-level storage
B. File-level storage
C. Block-level storage
D. Queue storage
Answer: C
Explanation: EBS = block storage, S3 = object, EFS = file.

2. When you stop an EC2 instance, what happens to its EBS volume by default?
A. Deleted immediately
B. Persists unless ‚Äúdelete on termination‚Äù is enabled
C. Encrypted automatically
D. Converted to S3 storage
Answer: B
Explanation: Root EBS volume persists unless delete-flag is set.

3. Which algorithm is used for EBS encryption?
A. RSA-2048
B. AES-128
C. AES-256
D. SHA-256
Answer: C
Explanation: AWS uses AES-256 with KMS.

4. Where does EBS encryption happen?
A. Inside the EBS volume
B. On the EC2 host
C. On S3
D. In the client machine
Answer: B
Explanation: Encryption happens on the server (EC2 hypervisor layer).

5. Which of the following gets encrypted automatically when an EBS encrypted volume is used?
A. Data in the instance RAM
B. Snapshots
C. Security groups
D. IAM roles
Answer: B
Explanation: Encrypted volume ‚Üí encrypted snapshot ‚Üí encrypted new volumes.

6. You want to attach one EBS volume to multiple EC2 instances simultaneously. Which volume type is required?
A. gp2
B. gp3
C. io1
D. io2
Answer: D
Explanation: Only io2 supports Multi-Attach.

7. To attach an EBS volume to an EC2 instance, what must match?
A. VPC IDs
B. AMI IDs
C. Availability Zone
D. Region
Answer: C
Explanation: EBS volumes are AZ-scoped, not region-scoped.

8. What happens if you lose your EC2 private key (.pem)?
A. AWS support can recover it
B. You can download it again
C. You cannot recover it
D. You can regenerate it on instance
Answer: C
Explanation: Lost private key = zero recovery.

9. How is the public key injected into a Linux EC2 instance?
A. IAM role
B. Stored in S3
C. Placed in ~/.ssh/authorized_keys during first boot
D. Sent via email
Answer: C

10. Which is true about EC2 key pairs?
A. Private key stored by AWS
B. Public key stored by user
C. Private key stored by user
D. You can recover private key anytime
Answer: C
Explanation: AWS keeps public, you keep private.

11. You want to encrypt an existing unencrypted EBS volume. What is the correct method?
A. Turn on encryption in-place
B. Reboot instance
C. Snapshot ‚Üí Copy snapshot (encrypt) ‚Üí Create new volume
D. Use IAM policy
Answer: C
Explanation: Only snapshot-copy-encrypt works.

12. Which of the following can be modified on a live EBS volume?
A. Size only
B. Size + IOPS + Volume Type
C. Nothing; must stop instance
D. Only IOPS
Answer: B
Explanation: EBS allows live modifications.

13. Encrypted and unencrypted EBS volumes can be attached to the same EC2 instance?
A. Yes
B. No
Answer: A
Explanation: They can coexist. Exam trick.

14. When you take an unencrypted snapshot of a volume, it will be:
A. Always encrypted
B. Always unencrypted
C. Encrypted automatically if volume > 100 GB
D. Randomly encrypted
Answer: B
Explanation: Snapshot inherits encryption state.

15. To SSH into a Linux EC2 instance, which file is required?
A. .txt
B. .pem
C. .ppk
D. .crt
Answer: B
Explanation: EC2 uses .pem keys.



What is EC2 Instance Store?
Ephemeral local block storage directly attached to the physical host of the EC2 instance.
Temporary storage ‚Üí data lost if instance is stopped, terminated, or fails.
Unlike EBS (persistent), instance store ‚Üí non-persistent.

2. Why do we need Instance Store?
‚úî High Performance
Physically attached ‚Üí very low latency.
Ideal for high throughput, IO-intensive & temporary data.

‚úî Best Use Cases
Cache
Buffer
Scratch space
Temporary processing files
Applications that can recreate data
Big data processing / Hadoop
High-performance workloads

3. Important Characteristics
‚ùó Data Loss
Data disappears when:
Instance stops
Instance terminates
Host fails
Instance store volume is unmapped
‚ùó Not for Boot Volume
EC2 instance store cannot be used as OS boot disk.
Booting from instance store = slow + unreliable (exam reminder).

4. Limitations
Not available for all EC2 instance types
(e.g., T2, T3 don‚Äôt have instance store)
Capacity is fixed at launch time, cannot resize later.
No snapshots or persistent backup like EBS.
Must handle backup/recovery manually if needed.

5. Block Device Mapping
When launching an instance, you can configure instance store volumes using block device mapping.
Instance store ‚Üí appears as additional NVMe/SCSI devices.

6. Comparison with EBS
Feature                 	Instance Store                       	EBS
Persistence	               ‚ùå Temporary                	‚úî Persistent
Data Loss	                    On stop/terminate         	Retains data
Performance	                 Very high	                   High but less than instance store
Backup                     	Manual	                      Snapshots
Resize                      	‚ùå No                      	‚úî Yes
Boot Volume               	‚ùå Not recommended           	‚úî YES


7. When to Use Instance Store
Use when:
Data is non-critical
You need extreme IO speed
Application can recreate data
You need cheap, fast, temporary storage

Do NOT use when:
You need permanent storage
Data must survive stops/terminations
You require snapshots/backups

8. Key Exam Tricks
Instance store = ephemeral = temporary
Not all EC2 types have instance store
Data lost on stop/terminate
Can‚Äôt resize instance store
Best for cache/buffer/scratch

.

‚úÖ EC2 Instance Store ‚Äì MCQs (With Answers + Explanations)
1. EC2 Instance Store is best described as:
A. Persistent block storage
B. Temporary block storage attached to the physical server
C. Object storage for EC2
D. Network-attached storage
Answer: B
‚úî Instance Store = ephemeral local block storage physically attached to the host.

2. What happens to data stored on an Instance Store volume when an EC2 instance is stopped?
A. Data persists automatically
B. Data is moved to S3
C. Data is lost
D. Data is snapshot automatically
Answer: C
‚úî Instance store data is lost on stop/terminate.

3. Which of the following is a good use case for Instance Store?
A. Storing long-term backups
B. Database storage requiring persistence
C. Cache or temporary buffer
D. Storing AMIs
Answer: C
‚úî Cache/buffer/scratch space = ideal for instance store.

4. Can an EC2 Instance Store volume be resized after instance launch?
A. Yes
B. No
C. Only if encrypted
D. Only with Auto Scaling
Answer: B
‚úî Capacity is fixed at launch.

5. Which EC2 storage type supports snapshots?
A. Only instance store
B. Only EBS
C. Both EBS and instance store
D. None
Answer: B
‚úî Only EBS supports snapshots. Instance store does NOT.

6. Does every EC2 instance type come with Instance Store volumes?
A. Yes
B. No
C. Yes, but only in shared tenancy
D. Yes, but only if requested via support
nswer: B
‚úî Many instances (e.g., T2/T3) do not have instance store.

7. Instance Store volumes are physically located where?
A. On S3
B. On EBS servers
C. On the EC2 instance's host hardware
D. In another AZ

Answer: C
‚úî Instance store is direct-attached hardware storage.

8. Which statement is TRUE about EC2 Instance Store?
A. Data is replicated across AZs
B. Instance Store can be used as boot volume
C. Suitable for high-speed temporary data
D. Data survives instance termination
Answer: C
‚úî High-speed temporary storage for IO-intensive workloads.

9. If the physical host of EC2 fails, what happens to instance store data?
A. It is backed up automatically
B. It persists regardless
C. It is lost
D. It is moved to EBS
Answer: C
‚úî Host failure = instance store wiped out.

10. Which is NOT a recommended use case for Instance Store?
A. Temporary data
B. Hadoop clusters
C. Container scratch space
D. Storing critical persistent logs
Answer: D
‚úî Critical logs require EBS, not ephemeral storage.

11. Instance Store volume capacity:
A. Can be increased anytime
B. Can be decreased anytime
C. Is fixed at instance launch
D. Depends on AMI size
Answer: C
‚úî Cannot resize instance store.

12. What must you check before planning to use Instance Store?
A. AMI version
B. Whether instance type supports instance store
C. Region
D. VPC configuration

Answer: B
‚úî Some instance families (like T-series) don‚Äôt have instance store.

13. During instance launch, Instance Store volumes are attached through:
A. Elastic network interface mapping
B. Block device mapping
C. IAM role mapping
D. Route tables
Answer: B
‚úî Block device mapping = where you configure instance store.

14. Which characteristic makes Instance Store high-performance?
A. Integrated with S3
B. It uses NVMe/SATA drives physically attached
C. Data replication across hosts
D. Uses KMS encryption by default
Answer: B
‚úî Physical NVMe/SATA drives ‚Üí super low latency.

15. Instance Store is ideal for which scenario?
A. Long-term relational database
B. File storage requiring durability
C. Temporary scratch disk for processing
D. Storing API keys
Answer: C
‚úî Only for temporary, fast IO workloads.
